sec.p:
The NFκB model was characterized in a manner similar to that for the NFAT model. Using the parameters from Tables 2–4, the calcium concentration was fixed at 0.1 μM and the time evolution of the concentration of each species calculated until steady state values were observed. These concentrations were taken to be those of the steady state at rest (Table 6).TABLE 6.
